
CPAN = Comprehensive Perl Archive Network.

URL: → www.cpan.org, searching CPAN at → http://search.cpan.org/

Bug Reports: → https://rt.cpan.org[rt.cpan.org]

Info about an author: `http://search.cpan.org/~USERID` (for example → http://search.cpan.org/~rene/)

{ Contributing to CPAN

  First: read → http://www.cpan.org/modules/04pause.html[Pause FAQ]

}
{ PAUSE

  PAUSE = Perl (programming) Author Upload Server.

  Whenever anyone creates a Perl module that they think will be useful to the world, they register as a Perl developer at → http://www.cpan.org/modules/04pause.html[PAUSE] so that they can then upload their code to the CPAN.

}
links:
  → http://www.cpan.org/modules/02packages.details.txt.gz seems to contain a list of CPAN packages

sa:
  → development/languages/Perl/modules:
  → development/languages/Perl/CPAN[CPAN] and → development/languages/Perl/modules/CPAN/Mini[CPAN::Mini]
  
  → development/languages/Perl

  → development/languages/Perl/installation/directory/perl/bin/cpan[`cpan`] is a Perl script to easily interact with CPAN from the command line.
